subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of allotypic female (
Fig 8 G, I
).

Differing from the 
holotype
as follows. Postorbital carapace length 80.22% of total carapace length. Areola 5.6 times longer (
10.6 mm
) than wide (
1.9 mm
). Right antennal scale 7.0 mm long, 3.0 mm wide. Mesial surface of palm of right chela with two rows of tubercles, eight tubercles in mesial most row and seven tubercles in dorsomesial row. Opposable margin of dactyl with nine tubercles of nearly uniform size. Annulus ventralis as described in Diagnosis.
